Britain's food safety watchdog added another 146 products to a list of items tainted by a potentially cancer-causing dye in the country's largest food recall yet.
Cyprus health services have advised people not to eat foods imported from Britain that have contaminated an illegal dye named Sudan I.
The Food Standards Agency (FSA) extended the list of foods contaminated by carcinogenic colouring that it wants to recall from shop shelves and homes.
The foods, including soups, sauces and ready meals, have been distributed widely.
